abstract: Daniel-Andre Tande breaks 1998 ski jump record, leading  Norway to World Cup victory in Kuopio, Finland.

headline.print_headline: Norwegian Ski Jumper Sets a Record
headline.main: Norwegian Ski Jumper Sets a Record

snippet: Daniel-Andre Tande eclipsed the 1998 record for a ski jump on the Puijo hill in Kuopio, Finland, and led Norway to a World Cup team victory.
lead_paragraph: Daniel-Andre Tande eclipsed the 1998 record for a ski jump on the Puijo hill in Kuopio, Finland, and led Norway to a World Cup team victory.
